00:58:46.646 --> 00:58:47.776 A:middle
grabbable and slidable.

00:58:49.326 --> 00:58:50.926 A:middle
Another technique you can use is

00:58:50.926 --> 00:58:53.146 A:middle
to elevate interactive elements

00:58:53.146 --> 00:58:54.136 A:middle
to a separate plane.

00:58:54.566 --> 00:58:55.946 A:middle
So, if you have an interactive

00:58:55.946 --> 00:58:57.576 A:middle
element, lifting it up to a

00:58:57.626 --> 00:58:58.676 A:middle
separate plane can help

00:58:58.716 --> 00:59:00.286 A:middle
distinguish it from the content.

00:58:58.716 --> 00:59:00.286 A:middle
distinguish it from the content.

00:59:01.586 --> 00:59:03.006 A:middle
So, a good example of this is

00:59:03.006 --> 00:59:04.056 A:middle
our on/off switch.

00:59:04.496 --> 00:59:05.696 A:middle
We want to indicate that the

00:59:05.696 --> 00:59:07.136 A:middle
knob of the switch is grabbable,

00:59:07.586 --> 00:59:08.996 A:middle
so we elevate it to another

00:59:09.076 --> 00:59:09.396 A:middle
plane.

00:59:10.036 --> 00:59:11.656 A:middle
This helps visually separate it,

00:59:11.816 --> 00:59:13.316 A:middle
and indicate its draggable

00:59:13.316 --> 00:59:13.776 A:middle
nature.

00:59:14.696 --> 00:59:16.096 A:middle
So, floating elements,

00:59:16.456 --> 00:59:17.716 A:middle
interactive elements like this,

00:59:17.716 --> 00:59:19.406 A:middle
above the interface can help

00:59:19.556 --> 00:59:20.816 A:middle
indicate that they're grabbable.

00:59:21.506 --> 00:59:26.136 A:middle
Next, we can use behavior, you

00:59:26.136 --> 00:59:28.156 A:middle
know, to show rather than tell

00:59:28.516 --> 00:59:29.656 A:middle
to use-- how to use an

00:59:29.656 --> 00:59:30.136 A:middle
interface.

00:59:30.426 --> 00:59:32.356 A:middle
So, we can reinforce a dynamic

00:59:32.396 --> 00:59:33.526 A:middle
behavior with a static

00:59:33.526 --> 00:59:34.106 A:middle
animation.

00:59:35.006 --> 00:59:35.976 A:middle
So, an example of this is

00:59:36.006 --> 00:59:36.446 A:middle
Safari.

00:59:37.076 --> 00:59:39.166 A:middle
In Safari, we have this x icon

00:59:39.166 --> 00:59:40.456 A:middle
at the top left to close the

00:59:40.456 --> 00:59:41.816 A:middle
tab, and when you hit that

00:59:41.866 --> 00:59:43.646 A:middle
button, we slide the tab left to

00:59:43.646 --> 00:59:44.766 A:middle
indicate it's deleted.

00:59:45.596 --> 00:59:46.846 A:middle
This hints to me that I can

00:59:46.846 --> 00:59:48.576 A:middle
slide it myself to the left.

00:59:48.676 --> 00:59:50.536 A:middle
And, accomplish the same action

00:59:50.536 --> 00:59:52.116 A:middle
of deleting the tab through a

00:59:52.116 --> 00:59:52.586 A:middle
gesture.

00:59:53.436 --> 00:59:54.886 A:middle
So, by keeping the discrete

00:59:55.046 --> 00:59:56.246 A:middle
animation and the gesture

00:59:56.246 --> 00:59:58.786 A:middle
aligned, we can use one to teach

00:59:58.826 --> 01:00:00.246 A:middle
the other.

00:59:58.826 --> 01:00:00.246 A:middle
the other.

01:00:02.296 --> 01:00:03.196 A:middle
And, there's another technique

01:00:03.196 --> 01:00:04.166 A:middle
we can use, which is

01:00:04.566 --> 01:00:05.306 A:middle
explanations.

01:00:05.476 --> 01:00:07.196 A:middle
This is when you explicitly tell

01:00:07.196 --> 01:00:08.576 A:middle
users how to use a gesture.

01:00:09.666 --> 01:00:10.796 A:middle
So, this is best when used

01:00:10.796 --> 01:00:12.456 A:middle
sparingly, but it's best when

01:00:12.456 --> 01:00:14.196 A:middle
you have one gesture that's used

01:00:14.196 --> 01:00:15.766 A:middle
repeatedly in a bunch of places,

01:00:16.186 --> 01:00:18.216 A:middle
and you explain it once up

01:00:18.216 --> 01:00:19.246 A:middle
front, and then you just keep

01:00:19.286 --> 01:00:20.966 A:middle
using it, and keep reinforcing

01:00:20.966 --> 01:00:21.036 A:middle
it.

01:00:21.896 --> 01:00:23.136 A:middle
Don't use it for a gesture

01:00:23.136 --> 01:00:24.836 A:middle
that's used only intermittently.

01:00:24.836 --> 01:00:25.976 A:middle
People won't remember that.

01:00:26.946 --> 01:00:29.706 A:middle
Now, I want to talk a little bit

01:00:29.706 --> 01:00:31.786 A:middle
about fun and playfulness.

01:00:32.496 --> 01:00:33.606 A:middle
Because this is one of the most

01:00:33.606 --> 01:00:35.346 A:middle
important aspects of a fluid

01:00:35.346 --> 01:00:35.976 A:middle
interface.

01:00:36.366 --> 01:00:37.906 A:middle
And, it only happens when you

01:00:37.906 --> 01:00:39.076 A:middle
nail everything.

01:00:40.326 --> 01:00:42.196 A:middle
It's a natural consequence of a

01:00:42.196 --> 01:00:43.136 A:middle
fluid interface.

01:00:43.136 --> 01:00:44.056 A:middle
It's when the interface is

01:00:44.056 --> 01:00:45.656 A:middle
responding instantly and

01:00:45.656 --> 01:00:46.186 A:middle
satisfyingly.

01:00:46.506 --> 01:00:47.686 A:middle
When it's redirectable and

01:00:47.686 --> 01:00:48.216 A:middle
forgiving.

01:00:48.676 --> 01:00:49.956 A:middle
When the motion and gestures are

01:00:49.956 --> 01:00:50.496 A:middle
smooth.

01:00:50.496 --> 01:00:51.556 A:middle
And, everything we just talked

01:00:51.556 --> 01:00:51.816 A:middle
about.

01:00:52.426 --> 01:00:53.836 A:middle
The interface starts to feel in

01:00:53.976 --> 01:00:54.546 A:middle
sync with you.

01:00:55.336 --> 01:00:57.486 A:middle
And, something magical happens

01:00:57.486 --> 01:00:58.996 A:middle
where you don't feel like you

01:00:58.996 --> 01:01:00.446 A:middle
need to learn the interface, you

01:00:58.996 --> 01:01:00.446 A:middle
need to learn the interface, you

01:01:00.546 --> 01:01:01.836 A:middle
feel like you're discovering the

01:01:01.836 --> 01:01:02.326 A:middle
interface.

01:01:03.806 --> 01:01:06.016 A:middle
And so, we think it's great when

01:01:06.016 --> 01:01:08.026 A:middle
we allow people to discover the

01:01:08.026 --> 01:01:09.026 A:middle
interface through play.

01:01:09.026 --> 01:01:10.076 A:middle
And, it doesn't even feel like

01:01:10.076 --> 01:01:11.216 A:middle
they're learning it, it feels

01:01:11.216 --> 01:01:11.626 A:middle
fun.

01:01:12.876 --> 01:01:15.436 A:middle
So, people love playing with

01:01:15.436 --> 01:01:15.836 A:middle
stuff.

01:01:16.146 --> 01:01:18.176 A:middle
So, we think it's great to play

01:01:18.176 --> 01:01:19.936 A:middle
into our natural fiddle factor.

01:01:20.696 --> 01:01:22.486 A:middle
You know, play is our mind's

01:01:22.486 --> 01:01:24.146 A:middle
internalizing the feel of an

01:01:24.146 --> 01:01:24.646 A:middle
interface.

01:01:25.356 --> 01:01:26.306 A:middle
So, it's great when we're

01:01:26.306 --> 01:01:27.256 A:middle
building this stuff, when we're

01:01:27.256 --> 01:01:29.066 A:middle
prototyping it, just to build

01:01:29.066 --> 01:01:29.646 A:middle
it.

01:01:29.646 --> 01:01:30.736 A:middle
You know, play with it yourself.

01:01:30.796 --> 01:01:32.176 A:middle
See how you fiddle with it.

01:01:32.266 --> 01:01:33.426 A:middle
Hand it to others see how they

01:01:33.426 --> 01:01:33.976 A:middle
play with it.

01:01:34.376 --> 01:01:35.486 A:middle
And, think about how you can

01:01:35.486 --> 01:01:37.536 A:middle
reinforce that with something

01:01:37.536 --> 01:01:39.106 A:middle
like an animation, or behavior,

01:01:39.106 --> 01:01:39.926 A:middle
an explanation.

01:01:41.336 --> 01:01:43.006 A:middle
And, it's surprising how far

01:01:43.126 --> 01:01:45.076 A:middle
play can go, and having

01:01:45.076 --> 01:01:46.726 A:middle
interface teach itself to

01:01:46.726 --> 01:01:47.056 A:middle
people.

01:01:47.626 --> 01:01:51.486 A:middle
Let's talk a little bit about

01:01:51.486 --> 01:01:52.696 A:middle
fluidity as a medium.

01:01:53.216 --> 01:01:54.146 A:middle
How we actually go about

01:01:54.206 --> 01:01:55.056 A:middle
building this stuff.

01:01:55.666 --> 01:01:56.716 A:middle
You know, we think interfaces

01:01:56.716 --> 01:01:58.426 A:middle
like this are a unique medium,

01:01:58.426 --> 01:01:59.426 A:middle
and it's important that we

01:01:59.616 --> 01:02:00.606 A:middle
approach it right.

01:01:59.616 --> 01:02:00.606 A:middle
approach it right.

01:02:02.376 --> 01:02:04.296 A:middle
So, the first thing is to design

01:02:04.296 --> 01:02:05.356 A:middle
the interactions to be

01:02:05.396 --> 01:02:07.036 A:middle
inseparable from the visuals,

01:02:07.616 --> 01:02:08.936 A:middle
not an afterthought.

01:02:09.566 --> 01:02:11.506 A:middle
The interaction design should be

01:02:11.506 --> 01:02:12.776 A:middle
done in concert with the

01:02:12.776 --> 01:02:13.196 A:middle
visuals.

01:02:13.196 --> 01:02:14.166 A:middle
You shouldn't be able to even

01:02:14.306 --> 01:02:15.776 A:middle
tell when one ends and another

01:02:15.776 --> 01:02:16.226 A:middle
begins.

01:02:17.466 --> 01:02:18.526 A:middle
And, it's really important that

01:02:18.526 --> 01:02:19.926 A:middle
we build demos of this stuff.

01:02:19.926 --> 01:02:21.326 A:middle
The interactive demo we think is

01:02:21.326 --> 01:02:23.006 A:middle
really worth a million static

01:02:23.046 --> 01:02:23.476 A:middle
designs.

01:02:23.926 --> 01:02:25.766 A:middle
Not just to show other people,

01:02:25.996 --> 01:02:27.806 A:middle
but to also understand the true

01:02:27.806 --> 01:02:29.016 A:middle
nature of the interface

01:02:29.016 --> 01:02:29.606 A:middle
yourself.

01:02:30.996 --> 01:02:33.646 A:middle
And, when you prototype this

01:02:33.646 --> 01:02:35.806 A:middle
stuff, it's so valuable for you

01:02:35.806 --> 01:02:36.846 A:middle
because you get to almost

01:02:36.846 --> 01:02:38.466 A:middle
discover the interface as you're

01:02:38.506 --> 01:02:38.886 A:middle
building it.

01:02:39.696 --> 01:02:40.436 A:middle
You know, this technique is

01:02:40.436 --> 01:02:41.796 A:middle
actually how we built the iPhone

01:02:41.886 --> 01:02:42.566 A:middle
10 interface.

01:02:43.886 --> 01:02:45.016 A:middle
And, it's really important

01:02:45.016 --> 01:02:46.636 A:middle
because it also sets a goal for

01:02:46.636 --> 01:02:47.406 A:middle
the implementation.

01:02:47.826 --> 01:02:49.416 A:middle
We're so lucky here at Apple

01:02:49.416 --> 01:02:50.596 A:middle
that we have this amazing

01:02:50.596 --> 01:02:52.056 A:middle
engineering team to build this

01:02:52.056 --> 01:02:53.386 A:middle
stuff, because it's really hard

01:02:53.386 --> 01:02:53.826 A:middle
to build.

01:02:53.936 --> 01:02:56.866 A:middle
And, it's so important also to

01:02:57.006 --> 01:02:58.126 A:middle
have that kind of magical

01:02:58.126 --> 01:02:59.706 A:middle
example that reminds yourself

01:02:59.706 --> 01:03:01.446 A:middle
and the engineering teams, and

01:02:59.706 --> 01:03:01.446 A:middle
and the engineering teams, and

01:03:01.586 --> 01:03:05.066 A:middle
yourselves that what it can feel

01:03:05.066 --> 01:03:05.746 A:middle
like, you know?

01:03:05.746 --> 01:03:08.276 A:middle
And, it's really important to,

01:03:08.486 --> 01:03:09.806 A:middle
kind of, remember, remind

01:03:09.806 --> 01:03:10.476 A:middle
yourself of that.

01:03:11.896 --> 01:03:15.086 A:middle
And, it makes-- when you

01:03:15.086 --> 01:03:16.426 A:middle
actually build it, it makes

01:03:16.426 --> 01:03:17.626 A:middle
something that's hard to copy,

01:03:17.896 --> 01:03:19.386 A:middle
and it gives your app a unique

01:03:19.426 --> 01:03:19.936 A:middle
character.

01:03:21.006 --> 01:03:27.286 A:middle
So, you know, multitouch is such

01:03:27.286 --> 01:03:28.726 A:middle
an amazing medium we all get to

01:03:28.726 --> 01:03:29.156 A:middle
play in.

01:03:30.196 --> 01:03:31.446 A:middle
We get to use technology to

01:03:31.446 --> 01:03:32.596 A:middle
interface with people at an

01:03:32.726 --> 01:03:34.106 A:middle
ancient, tactile level.

01:03:34.756 --> 01:03:36.126 A:middle
It's actually really cool.

01:03:38.206 --> 01:03:40.066 A:middle
You know, all those principles

01:03:40.066 --> 01:03:42.226 A:middle
we talked about today, they're

01:03:42.226 --> 01:03:43.616 A:middle
at the core of the design of the

01:03:43.746 --> 01:03:45.646 A:middle
iPhone 10 gestural interface,

01:03:46.336 --> 01:03:47.526 A:middle
you know, responsive,

01:03:47.526 --> 01:03:48.976 A:middle
redirectable, interruptible

01:03:48.976 --> 01:03:50.926 A:middle
gestures, dynamic motion,

01:03:51.306 --> 01:03:52.876 A:middle
elegant gesture handling.

01:03:53.636 --> 01:03:55.056 A:middle
In a lot of ways, it's kind of

01:03:55.056 --> 01:03:56.486 A:middle
the embodiment of what we think

01:03:56.486 --> 01:03:57.646 A:middle
a fluid interface could be.

01:03:58.996 --> 01:04:01.246 A:middle
When we align the interface to

01:03:58.996 --> 01:04:01.246 A:middle
When we align the interface to

01:04:01.246 --> 01:04:02.586 A:middle
the way we think and move,

01:04:03.376 --> 01:04:04.756 A:middle
something kind of magical

01:04:04.756 --> 01:04:05.166 A:middle
happens.

01:04:05.986 --> 01:04:07.796 A:middle
It really stops feeling like a

01:04:07.796 --> 01:04:09.906 A:middle
computer, and starts feeling

01:04:09.906 --> 01:04:11.596 A:middle
like a seamless extension of us.

01:04:14.416 --> 01:04:16.206 A:middle
You know, as we design the

01:04:16.276 --> 01:04:18.336 A:middle
future of interfaces, we think

01:04:18.336 --> 01:04:19.776 A:middle
it's really important to try and

01:04:20.056 --> 01:04:21.716 A:middle
capture our humanity in the

01:04:21.716 --> 01:04:22.626 A:middle
technology like this.

01:04:23.626 --> 01:04:24.416 A:middle
So, that one of the most

01:04:24.416 --> 01:04:26.596 A:middle
important tools of humankind is

01:04:26.596 --> 01:04:28.966 A:middle
not a burden, but a pleasure and

01:04:28.966 --> 01:04:30.086 A:middle
a delight to use.

01:04:30.966 --> 01:04:31.956 A:middle
Thank you very much.

